The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at the Detroit Economic Club in Michigan. Pence discussed the state of the American economy and highlighted the accomplishments of the Trump administration, such as tax cuts, deregulation, and job creation. He also spoke about the importance of passing the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA) and addressing trade issues with China. Pence expressed concern about the policy proposals put forth by Democratic presidential candidates and emphasized the need to continue the current economic progress. He concluded by expressing confidence in the future of the American economy and the principles that have made the country prosperous.